8437: // of a GMSA cred spec. In general, those shouldn't be more than a few hundred bytes,
8438: // so we want to give plenty of room here while still providing an upper bound.
8439: // The runAsUserName field will be used to execute the given container's entrypoint, and
8440: // it can be formatted as "DOMAIN/USER", where the DOMAIN is optional, maxRunAsUserNameDomainLength
8441: // is the max character length for the user's DOMAIN, and maxRunAsUserNameUserLength
8442: // is the max character length for the USER itself. Both the DOMAIN and USER have their
8443: // own restrictions, and more information about them can be found here:
8444: // https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/909264/naming-conventions-in-active-directory-for-computers-domains-sites-and
