eged containers at baseline level\n  - CheckPrivileged(): Returns baseline level check\n  - privileged_1_0(): Validates no container has privileged=true\n\n- check_capabilities_baseline.go: Restricts capabilities to default set at baseline level\n  - CheckCapabilitiesBaseline(): Baseline level check\n  - capabilitiesBaseline_1_0(): Validates only allowed capabilities (AUDIT_WRITE, CHOWN, DAC_OVERRIDE, etc.) can be added\n\n- check_capabilities_restricted.go: Requires dropping ALL capabilities and only allowing NET_BIND_SERVICE at restricted level\n  - CheckCapabilitiesRestricted(): Restricted level check\n  - capabilitiesRestricted_1_22(): Validates ALL is dropped and only NET_BIND_SERVICE can be added\n  - capabilitiesRestricted_1_25(): Windows pod exemption support\n\n- check_seccompProfile_baseline.go: Baseline seccomp profile validation\n  - CheckSeccompProfileBaseline(): Validates against deprecated seccomp annotations\n  - seccompProfileBaseline_1_0(): Checks deprecated annotation usage\n  - seccompProfileBaseline_1_19(): Validates seccompProfile field values\n\n- check_seccompProfile_restricted.go: Restricted seccomp profile enforcement\n  - CheckSeccompProfileRestricted(): Requires RuntimeDefault or Localhost profiles\n  - seccompProfileRestricted_1_19(): Validates only RuntimeDefault or Localhost allowed\n  - seccompProfileRestricted_1_25(): Windows pod exemption support\n\n**3. Security Context Accessors (pkg/securitycontext/accessors.go):**\n- RunAsNonRoot(): Accessor for pod and container-level runAsNonRoot field\n- Privileged(): Accessor for container-level privileged field\n- Capabilities(): Accessor for container-level capabilities field\n- SeccompProfile(): Accessor for pod and container-level seccompProfile field\n\n**4. Runtime Verification (pkg/kubelet/kuberuntime/):**\n- security_context_others.go - verifyRunAsNonRoot(): Runtime validation that pod/container actually runs as non-root\n- security_context_windows.go - verifyRunAsNonRoot(): Windows-specific runtime verification\n- helpers.go:\n  - fieldSeccompProfile(): Converts internal seccomp profile to runtime API format\n  - getSeccompProfile(): Retrieves effective seccomp profile from pod and container contexts\n\nThese validation components work together to enforce pod security policies at API admission time and verify compliance at runtime."
